story.title: Rabid - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: When squirrels suddenly start attacking people, Stephanie’s entire existence is in danger...
story.creator: web-uploader
story.postPaywallNotification: What terrifying thing did Stephanie see? Keep reading RABID to find out.

messages.text: Archer, are you there?
What’s up, babe?
I’m at the hospital.
What?! Are you OK?
A squirrel bit me!
It’s like it…snapped.
I had to get a rabies shot.
Wow, that’s crazy. Squirrels almost never bite.
Did you do anything to set it off?
No! I was just sitting on a bench in Prospect Park.
And this squirrel started glaring at me.
When I got up, it lunged for my ankle. I was bleeding!
Must have been rabid. Good thing you got a shot.
And I’ll need to get more. SO annoying!
Are you in any pain?
I’m just a little sore from the bite and the shot.
The doctors put a bandage on my ankle. The bleeding stopped.
Do you want to come here and recuperate?
My mom knows a lot about squirrels.
A long time ago, she found an injured squirrel and nursed it back to health.
It was in our apartment for months
That’s kinda weird.
But Archer, I’m just going to stay here.
You know your mother and I don’t really get along.
Once she gets to know you, I’m sure that’ll change.
I don’t know about that…
When are you going to move out, anyway?
You ARE 28.
And you have a good job. You can afford it.
I’ve been looking! Just haven’t found the right place yet.
Finally! The doctors said I could leave.
Can you stay with me tonight, Arch?
Remember, I’m going to be gone for a whole week!
And this whole thing with the squirrel was traumatic.
Poor sweetie.
I’ll come over in a few hours to take care of you.
But first I need to help Mom put up some shelves in the kitchen.
Such a good son. See you soon! Love you.
Love you too.
one hour later
OMG Archer!
What?!
On my way home, a block from the hospital…
A group of teenage girls was walking by.
And a squirrel just lunged at one of them!
Her leg was bleeding! They had to take her right to the hospital!
Good thing it was only a block away.
WTF? Was it the same squirrel?
I don’t think so. That other squirrel was a mile away.
What’s going on here?!
Warning: Authorities are reporting multiple squirrel attacks across Brooklyn and Queens. Be aware of your surroundings. Wear thick clothing around arms and legs. Stay inside if possible.
You’d better stay where you are, Archie.
Yeah, Mom says I’m safer here.
She says the squirrels are fine by the apartment building.
She was just feeding some…and talking to them.
Do you want to come here?
No! I don’t want to go outside.
Plus, your mom wouldn’t want me there.
Right. Sorry.
I’m so glad I’m leaving on that business trip tomorrow.
I’m going to RUN from my door to the Uber.
Man, this is crazy.
You’re sure you’re OK to travel, especially after that bite?
Yeah, I feel a lot better.
OK, I love you! Have a great trip!
And be careful.
Love you too. See you soon.
one week later
I’m back 😘
Hey! I missed you so much.
Can’t wait to…
To what?
Mmmmmmm.
Where are you?
On my way home from JFK. Just got off the subway.
Still no more reports of angry squirrels, right?
Right. It was just that one night.
They’re saying it was some kind of electrical surge.
It messed with the squirrels’ brains, apparently.
And none of the other animals were bothered by it?
Apparently not.
That doesn’t make any sense.
I’m just telling you what the experts said.
Hmmmm. Well, I’m just glad it was a one-time thing.
How about you jump in a cab and come see me right now?
I want to feel those lips of yours…
Sorry, no can do.
My mom just fixed dinner. I’ll come over right after that.
five minutes later
Oh my God. Archer.
What is it, Steph?
I just turned onto my block.
There’s a squirrel in the middle of the sidewalk.
It’s giving me this look…
Like it wants to kill me.
